6.05pm From 92 for 4 in 20.1 overs, Australia finish at 324 for 8. New Zealand's bowling, especially at the slog overs was poor and their fielding was probably worse. Steven Smith led the way with the bat for the hosts, hitting 164 - the highest individual score at the SCG - and found able support from Travis Head, who made a half-century in his first ODI at home. Then Wade who was promoted ahead of Maxwell applied the finishing touches with drills and scoops. Be back in 30 minutes or thereabouts for the chase.

Asgar: "After 50 overs, NZ still have that review left which they did not use against Steve Smith!!! " ---- Had NZ activated their review when Smith was rapped on the pads by Boult, the Australia captain would have been dismissed for 14. At the start of the same over, he was dropped on 13 by Watling diving to his left
